# Seneschal ops watchdog config — operator-managed env.
#
# Install location on fin4: /etc/seneschal/ops-monitor.env
# Mode: 600 root:root
#
# Everything below is optional. With nothing set the watchdog still
# runs (every 10 min via seneschal-ops-monitor.timer), writes its
# state to /var/lib/seneschal-ops-monitor/state.json (consumed by
# /v1/ops/health and the stats page) and logs to journalctl. The
# only thing you lose is push notifications.

# ── Telegram alerting (recommended) ─────────────────────────────
# 1. Talk to @BotFather, /newbot, follow prompts. Save the token.
# 2. Start a chat with your new bot from @OrknetP (the bot has to
#    have spoken to you first before it can DM you). Send any
#    message.
# 3. curl "https://api.telegram.org/bot$BOT_TOKEN/getUpdates" — find
#    your chat in the `result[*].message.chat.id` field. Numeric
#    integer for private chats, negative for group chats.
# 4. Drop them in here, chmod 600, then `systemctl start
#    seneschal-ops-monitor.service` to force a fresh tick — you'll
#    get an "Initial watchdog state" message if anything's degraded,
#    nothing otherwise.
#
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456:ABC-DEF1234ghIkl-zyx57W2v1u123ew11
# TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=123456789

# ── Optional: override the units / scripts that are checked ─────
# Comma-separated. For unit names append ":cadenceSec" to enable
# the timer-staleness check (omit the colon for long-running
# services like the REST server). Script presence is verified by
# existence + READability — .mjs scripts run via `node script.mjs`
# don't need the +x bit (and rsync deploys routinely drop it).
# The values below mirror the in-code defaults; uncomment only to
# diverge from them.
#
# SENESCHAL_OPS_UNITS=seneschal-data-rest.service,seneschal-data-mcp.service,seneschal-private-watch-poller.service:180,seneschal-crypto-recv-poller.service:60,seneschal-income-poller.service:3600,seneschal-paymaster-sweep-check.service:86400,seneschal-backup.service:86400
# SENESCHAL_OPS_SCRIPTS=/opt/seneschal-data-api/scripts/private-watch-poller.mjs,/opt/seneschal-data-api/scripts/crypto-recv-poller.mjs,/opt/seneschal-data-api/scripts/income-poller.mjs,/opt/seneschal-data-api/scripts/paymaster-sweep-check.mjs,/opt/seneschal-data-api/scripts/publish-docs.sh

# ── Optional: HTTP probes ────────────────────────────────────────
# JSON array of probe specs (see runProbe in src/ops-monitor.js), or
# the literal string "none" to disable on hosts without the fin1
# tunnel. The defaults probe the three reverse-tunnel forwards
# (monerod 18081, zebra 8232, NFPT 3555 on loopback) and assert the
# public paywall still answers 402 with a payment-required header.
# Uncomment only to diverge.
#
# SENESCHAL_OPS_PROBES=[{"name":"tunnel-monerod","url":"http://127.0.0.1:18081/get_info","expectBodyIncludes":["\"synchronized\": true"]},{"name":"paywall-402","url":"https://api.seneschal.space/v1/q/xmr/height","expectStatus":402,"expectHeader":"payment-required"}]
# SENESCHAL_OPS_PROBES=none

# ── Optional: state file path ───────────────────────────────────
# SENESCHAL_OPS_STATE_FILE=/var/lib/seneschal-ops-monitor/state.json
